column5: Who else felt the earthquake that just happened here?
me   quote name='Bernie' date='23 June 2010 - 01:46 PM' timestamp='1277315207' post='478623'] Who else felt the earthquake that just happened here?
Had a car on the hoist. It was sure moving around!
We did in St Catharines, just a small vibration.
The house was shakin here in the Ottawa Valley---tried to convince the wife that was me

Ok...This is gonna sound weird. I'm sitting in my office, and an employee calls me who is at lunch and asked me if i felt that...I said that I did not feel anything, he said his car was rocking back and forth...The weird thing is...I'm in Cleveland !

Well Bernie.. I was sitting in an airplane suspended from the steel beam above and two block and tackles... 2 days to go on it after 2 months and I thought the hangar was coming down on it! If that wasn't bad enough.. a tornado roared thru 5 hours later...

Just like Bushart, over here in Ottawa I felt it pretty good. Was on a second floor of a house/office and it felt like the building was gonna come down.  Pretty scary yet really neat.  Wayne, I hope there is not too much damage at your place.Hope all is well around you.
I was on the water.. didn't feel a thing. I kinda wanted to feel it though, not a usual thing thats for sure.
